            <div class="text9">
                <p>Artist: Miguel Witzke Pereira </p>
                <p>Title: <em>The Sacrifice: bottom</em></p>
                <p>
                    Miguel Witzke Pereira’s work stands in between sculpture, choreography and performance.
                    He questions it by fusing and dividing the boundaries of them all. 
                    Either in the material, the way in which they are set in space or through the interaction with the audience.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    How can performance be sculptural and how can sculpture be performative?
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    It is by taking fragments of situations that he questions the body as material, 
                    where it stands in relation to the objects and how does the object make the body become seemingly complete.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    In “The Sacrifice”, the question of one active part imposing passivity on the other and vice versa is the activator of the work. 
                    Here, the body is inserted into the material and the material fully detains the body creating a physical and mental commitment seen as sculptural. 
                    It is the audience’s sensitivity which will determine which it is for them a trap or a gratification of oneself.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    miguelwitzkepereira.com
                </p>
